race.comment: CORONA LAD (12) doesn't win out of turn but put in a good effort off a freshen up last time back to this trip at Horsham having been stretched over further prior. Another with a tough draw but if the speed is on he'll be home hard. BRUNG KING (3) was good under the big weight fresh at Bendigo when sticking on gamely for second. He looks certain to improve off that effort having only 1 jumpout prior to this resuming effort. He ticks plenty of boxes with his second-up record, being out in trip and the handy barrier. Hasn't won for a while, though everything points to a forward showing. SHE'S PRETTY RICH (8) will find this a little easier than what she's been racing in recently and the sting out of the ground is no issue. Live chance. FREAK OF NATURE (7) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back.
